# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Secrets for the guided deploy (`npm run setup`). Copy to `.env` and fill in.
# `.env` is gitignored — never commit real seeds.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Deployer mnemonic (12/24-word sr25519 seed). Deploys the contracts; its
# account must be funded with the network's native token.
DEPLOYER_SEED="your twelve word mnemonic goes here ..."

# Publisher mnemonic for the DotNS publish (owns the DotNS domains). Optional —
# if unset, the deployer seed is reused for publishing too.
# DOTNS_MNEMONIC="your publisher mnemonic ..."

# ── Summit (PCF deploy target) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Summit is a first-class network key in this fork (packages/shared/host/
# networks.ts), so the Summit deploy is simply:
#
#   NETWORK=summit npm run deploy:multicall
#   NETWORK=summit npm run deploy:festival
#   npm run build:admin    -- --dotenv .env.summit     # VITE_NETWORK=summit baked
#   npm run build:attendee -- --dotenv .env.summit
#
# All Summit chain coordinates (RPCs, genesis hashes, SUM/10dp, the
# https://summit-ipfs.polkadot.io gateway) are baked into the `summit` registry
# entry — no CUSTOM_* needed, and the browser bundle resolves `summit` (the
# `custom` path is Node-only and throws at app boot, see networks.ts note).
#
# Optional: enable the DotNS personhood/ownership advisory on Summit. Summit's
# DotNS addresses are already wired into scripts/lib/dotns-check.ts when
# NETWORK=summit, so no extra env is required for the advisory.
#
# App leg (publish both SPAs → Summit Bulletin) runs on the VM via the
# polkadot-app-deploy CLI, NOT this repo's deploy.yml workflow (which targets the
# dead paritytech/bulletin-deploy ref + forces --publish; Summit has no
# Publisher). See FESTIVAL_DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md §5–6.

# ── Custom network only (network=custom in deploy.config.json) ──
# Define your own chain. Genesis hashes are optional (deploy connects via WS).
# NOTE: the `custom` path only drives the Node deploy/build scripts — the BROWSER
# bundle (constants.ts) cannot resolve `custom` and will throw at boot. For
# Summit, prefer NETWORK=summit above. Kept here for ad-hoc/dev chains.
# CUSTOM_MAIN_WS=wss://your-asset-hub/rpc
# CUSTOM_MAIN_GENESIS=0x...
# CUSTOM_BULLETIN_WS=wss://your-bulletin/rpc
# CUSTOM_BULLETIN_GENESIS=0x...
# CUSTOM_IPFS_GATEWAY=https://your-ipfs-gateway
# CUSTOM_NATIVE_SYMBOL=UNIT
# CUSTOM_NATIVE_DECIMALS=12
# CUSTOM_DISPLAY_NAME=My Network
